Files:
- platform/mcp-server/src/extension-protocol.ts (extract writeAllAdapterFiles from sendSyncFull)
- platform/mcp-server/src/reload.ts (call writeAllAdapterFiles in reloadCore)

Context:
Adapter IIFE files are written to ~/.opentabs/extension/adapters/ by writeAdapterFile() (in adapter-files.ts). Currently, the ONLY place that calls writeAdapterFile in batch is sendSyncFull() (extension-protocol.ts line 62-132). sendSyncFull is called from:
1. reloadCore (reload.ts line 340-341) — guarded by `if (isExtensionConnected(state))`
2. wsOpen handler (http-routes.ts line 699) — when extension connects
3. file watcher callbacks (reload.ts lines 178, 192)

Since reloadCore guards the call with isExtensionConnected, adapter files are never written during startup if the extension hasn't connected yet. This causes 'Could not load file' errors when the extension connects and tries to inject adapters.

Changes:

1. In extension-protocol.ts, extract lines 62-93 of sendSyncFull into a new function:
```
const writeAllAdapterFiles = async (state: ServerState): Promise<Map<string, string>> => {
  const pluginList = Array.from(state.registry.plugins.values());
  await ensureAdaptersDir(state);
  const currentPluginNames = new Set(pluginList.map(p => p.name));
  await cleanupStaleAdapterFiles(currentPluginNames);
  const writePromise = Promise.allSettled(pluginList.map(p => writeAdapterFile(p.name, p.iife, p.iifeSourceMap)));
  const timeout = timeoutRace<null>(null, ADAPTER_WRITE_TIMEOUT_MS);
  const writeResults = await Promise.race([writePromise, timeout.promise]);
  timeout.cancel();
  const adapterFileMap = new Map<string, string>();
  // ... collect results into adapterFileMap (same logic as current lines 78-93)
  return adapterFileMap;
};
```

2. Refactor sendSyncFull to call writeAllAdapterFiles:
```
const sendSyncFull = async (state: ServerState): Promise<void> => {
  const adapterFileMap = await writeAllAdapterFiles(state);
  // ... rest of sendSyncFull (build payload and send to extension)
};
```

3. In reload.ts, add an eager call in reloadCore after resetStaleReviewedVersions (around line 299), BEFORE the isExtensionConnected check:
```
// Write adapter files eagerly so they exist on disk before the extension connects.
try {
  await writeAllAdapterFiles(state);
} catch (err) {
  log.warn('Failed to write adapter files:', err);
}
```

4. Export writeAllAdapterFiles from extension-protocol.ts and import it in reload.ts.

The writes are idempotent — writeAdapterFile uses content-hashed filenames, so calling it twice with the same IIFE content writes the same file. The second call from sendSyncFull (if the extension is connected) is effectively a no-op since the files already exist.

Constraints:
- Do NOT change the sendSyncFull interface or its WS message format
- Do NOT remove the sendSyncFull call from the isExtensionConnected block — it still needs to send the WS message
- Do NOT change writeAdapterFile or cleanupStaleAdapterFiles in adapter-files.ts
- Do NOT change the wsOpen handler in http-routes.ts
- The log message 'Sent sync.full to extension with N plugin(s)' must still appear when the extension is connected

